Uber Eats was already disdainful in their handling of their “technical difficulties” on mistakenly doubling up of an item I’d requested. Still waiting for that money back. But honestly the food here is gross. The shrimp scampi linguine is inedible. The excess amount of cheese is gag worthy. What are you trying to mask? The shrimp and scungilli (conch) was ordered. Yes, scungilli (conch) is supposed to be briny, not metallic. The taste of the metal can that it was poured out of is still lingering in my mouth. Not ideal.  The only time I truly ever write reviews is for others to steer clear. This is the second time I’ve done this.

This place is bigger and the service wasnt any better. Celebrating my birthday and the service wasnt all that. As we got there, the manager was leaving. We had 3 snapple at $2 each and on bill was marked for 5 of them. The older Spanish guy with glasses not so friendly either. Plus we left him a really nice tip. I didnt notice till we left but it's ok. I believe in Karma, that wasnt cool. You keep doing this and your gonna be left without a job. Never came by to check on us or see if we needed anything. Never offered more bread or sauce. Nothing, was very surprised by that. We all said the other location had way better service. We didnt wanna ruin the evening with any coffee or anything so we went to a nice coffee shop in the area & that service was Fabulous. No smiles, friendliness or anything. It looked like they didnt even like their job. I always say, if you dont like your job, it will show. Just alittle advise, treat people the way you like to be treated esp, if your out with your family. Was trying to Express our company with the 3 sauces and the guy brought out 2. I had to ask for the third sauce, that's what this restaurant is known for. So from the beginning it wasnt cool. I hope with the extra add on, you think you got over but in reality just shows how not nice you are as a waiter. Not cool at all.

All I have to say is Thank God these chefs have the passion they do to open up such a wonderful place. I used to go to Little Charles Clam Bar as a kid with my father and when they closed I was upset. They had the best Calamari with Hot Sauce ever. No Place in New York had the Hot Sauce they did.  After searching for years  I am so happy to find that the Chefs brought true authentic recipes that never change and  also glad that they kept that true clam bar feel and taste like Little Charles had, and took it in there own hands to open up a place like this again. Don't change a thing Chefs. Your guys rock!!! and blow away Vincent's and Umberto's,. Finally Chefs that stay true and cook from there heart. I will def recommend Desy's to all my friends that used to go to Charles.
